Soy sauce
bread 2 slices torn into small pieces
Puff pastry

Key: &gt; a little (~1/2 tsp), &gt;&gt; some (1 tsp), &gt;&gt;&gt; pleanty (~3 tsp)




Brown finely chopped onion. Then add garlic, chilli and ginger until aromatic. Add spices and soy sauce and wait for smell to change.
Add eggplant and \(\approx 1\) cup water, allow to soften. Then add tofu and cook until spice begins to absorb.
Separately, mince beans (e.g. with a fork) until forms a smoothish paste, with some chunks remaining.
Stir the beans into the tofu/eggplant mix. Add bread.
Put mix into pastry and bake on \(180^oC\) until brown.












